headline.main: Anne O'Hare McCormick Is Dead; Member of Times Editorial Board; Pulitzer Prize Winner in 1937 Interpreted News in Her Column, 'Abroad' ANNE M'CORI)III3K: OF TIMES IS DEAD

abstract: dies, 72; career; por; Pres Eisenhower, A H Sulzberger tributes
snippet: Mrs. Anne O'Hare McCormick, a member of the editorial board of The New York Times, died yesterday at 6:50 P. M. in Doctors Hospital, which she entered as a patient on May 11. Her age was 72. She had lapsed into a coma in the late afternoon and did...
